				<span class="item-control blog-admin pid-721112219"><a style="border:none;" href="http://www.blogger.com/delete-comment.g?blogID=3896669&postID=3177943581704337110" title="Delete Comment" ><span class="delete-comment-icon">&nbsp;</span></a></span>
			</div>
			
			<div class="blogComment">
				&nbsp;<br /><a name="4862836001144241863"></a> 
				Not possible unless dangerous.  This is not something Microsoft would want, so they won't co-operate, and their sincere co-operation would be absolutely necessary because OOXML is, despite all the pages and pages, seriously underspecified and anyway a "harmonized" format wouldn't fly if Microsoft didn't adopt it.<BR/><BR/>But there is one condition under which Microsoft *would* want it:  If they controlled it.  In which case it would just be a way of killing ODF.  They'd end up with a "harmonized" format for all the different word processors to use--that only Microsoft Word could use.<BR/><BR/>Rufus Polson<br />
